Investigation findings show that the subject firm is an employee-owned company operating as a cooperative which
produces softwood plywood.

New findings on reconsideration show a substantial decline in employment in fiscal year (FY) 1994 compared to FY 1993.
Sales and production declines occurred in FY 1994 compared to FY 1993.

The subject firms's fiscal year runs from July 1 to June 30. U.S. aggregate imports of soft plywood increased substantially
in 1993 compared to 1992.

